[size=150][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*] Three different default [i]translation engines[/i] can be selected to be used by the panel translator ([b]Bing translator[/b], [b]Google translator[/b] and [b]Yandex translator[/b]).
[*] Virtually any existent translation service could be added as a custom engine.
[*] Two different default [i]translation engines[/i] can be selected to be used as page translators ([b]Bing translator[/b] and [b]Google translator[/b]).
[*] More page translator custom engines can be added easily. This feature uses bookmarklets to perform page translations. [color=red][b]Be very careful!! Only use bookmarklets from [i]reputable sources[/i].[/b][/color] You can get customized bookmarklets from [url=http://labs.microsofttranslator.com/bookmarklet/]Bing/Microsoft translator bookmarklets[/url] and [url=http://translate.google.com/translate_buttons]Google translator bookmarklets[/url].
[*] Three different customizable hotkeys are available (Disabled by default). [list]
[*] [i][b]Ctrl/Cmd + Alt + t[/b][/i]: Translate selection
[*] [i][b]Ctrl/Cmd + Alt + p[/b][/i]: Translate current page
[*] [i][b]Ctrl/Cmd + Alt + v[/b][/i]: Translate clipboard content[/list]
[*] Languages to translate from/to can be selected from their respective menu lists inside the panel translation and inside the Page translator options. Most languages are supported by the three translation engines and those that are exclusive to an specific engine are marked ([b](B)[/b]ing, [b](G)[/b]oogle and [b](Y)[/b]andex ).
[*] The panel translator can be triggered in different ways to translate the selected text or the clipboard content.[list]
[*] From the page context menu by clicking [i]Translate selection[/i] or [i]Translate clipboard content[/i] menu items.
[*] From this button menu by clicking [i]Translate selection[/i] or [i]Translate clipboard content[/i] menu items.
[*] Automatically after selecting some text if the option [b]Translate on release[/b] is enabled. The [b]Ctrl/Cmd[/b] and/or [b]Alt[/b] keys can be required to trigger the panel. Both modifier keys can be configured to be used either independently or together.
[*] By assigning a click action to [b]Multi Translator[/b] button.[/list]
[*] The list of supported languages for the 3 main [i]translation engines[/i] is very long (119 languages in total). Languages can be hidden from the language selection menu inside the panel and the Page translator options by just right clicking on the language names.
[*] [b]Multi Translator[/b] button can be configured to perform various actions depending on click combinations.[list] [b]Possible click combinations[/b]
[*] Left click
[*] Middle click
[*] Ctrl/Cmd + Left click
[*] Shift + Left click
[*] Ctrl/Cmd + Shift + Left click[/list][list] [b]Possible actions[/b]
[*] Disabled. It disables the click combination on [b]Multi Translator[/b] button.
[*] Open main menu
[*] Translate selection.
[*] Translate current page.
[*] Translate clipboard content.
[*] Open page translation menu.[/list][list] [b]Default click combination actions[/b]
[*] [b]Left click:[/b] Open main menu
[*] [b]Middle click:[/b] Translate selection.
[*] [b]Ctrl/Cmd + Left click:[/b] Translate current page.
[*] [b]Shift + Left click:[/b] Translate clipboard content.
[*] [b]Ctrl/Cmd + Shift + Left click:[/b] Open page translation menu.[/list]
[*] An style sheet for XUL elements that can be used to customize the panel translator appearance.
[*] An style sheet for HTML elements that can be used to customize the translation services web pages. By default I added some tweaks that removes from the [b]Google Translator[/b] and [b]Bing Translator[/b] translated pages all tooltips used to show the translated text in its original language. [b]This style sheet will affect all pages of those services opened in the browser.[/b][/list]

